Sentencas: Symmetrical solid oxide fuel cell (SSOFC) is one of efficient ways to simplify preparation process, reduce manufacturing cost, and improve redox stability and reliability.
Titulo: Performance of Pd-impregnated Sr1.9FeNb0.9Mo0.1O6-δ double perovskites as symmetrical electrodes for direct hydrocarbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Here, we report the performance of Sr-deficient Sr1.9FeNb0.9Mo0.1O6-delta (SFNM) double perovskites as symmetrical electrodes for direct-hydrocarbon solid oxide fuel cells and significant improvement of electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Performance of Pd-impregnated Sr1.9FeNb0.9Mo0.1O6-δ double perovskites as symmetrical electrodes for direct hydrocarbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The SFNM exhibits good structural stability, suitable thermal expansion coefficient and highly chemical compatibility with Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (SDC) and La0.9Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM) electrolytes in both air and 5% H-2/Ar atmospheres.
Titulo: Performance of Pd-impregnated Sr1.9FeNb0.9Mo0.1O6-δ double perovskites as symmetrical electrodes for direct hydrocarbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The area specific resistance of SFNM electrode is decreased by 3.6 and 8.4 times at 800 degrees C in air and H-2, respectively, as compared to the pristine Sr2FeNbO6-delta-electrode.
Titulo: Performance of Pd-impregnated Sr1.9FeNb0.9Mo0.1O6-δ double perovskites as symmetrical electrodes for direct hydrocarbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance is further improved by introducing a small amount of Pd to form Pd-impregnated SFNM composite electrode (Pd-SFNM).
Titulo: Performance of Pd-impregnated Sr1.9FeNb0.9Mo0.1O6-δ double perovskites as symmetrical electrodes for direct hydrocarbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The SSOFCs with Pd-SFNM after two-time impregnation treatments as the electrodes achieve impressive electrochemical performances in different fuels.
Titulo: Performance of Pd-impregnated Sr1.9FeNb0.9Mo0.1O6-δ double perovskites as symmetrical electrodes for direct hydrocarbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The Pd-SFNM symmetrical electrode reveals good electrochemical stability operating on CH4-CO2 mixed gas.
Titulo: Performance of Pd-impregnated Sr1.9FeNb0.9Mo0.1O6-δ double perovskites as symmetrical electrodes for direct hydrocarbon solid oxide fuel cells
